Module stincmale.idenator
Package stincmale.idenator.doc

Annotation Type NotThreadSafe

  • @Documented
@Target({TYPE,METHOD})
@Retention(CLASS)
public @interface NotThreadSafe
    An object of a type annotated with this annotation or a method annotated with this annotation should not be used(1) concurrently without additional synchronization or coordination on the part of a user; such objects, types and methods are called not thread-safe.

    This annotation can be useful in cases specified by ThreadSafe as well as in some cases where an explicit statement about the lack of thread-safety can help avoiding misunderstanding.

    This annotation does not forbid a type to be thread-safe but rather informs a user that it may be not safe to use an object or method concurrently without additional synchronization or coordination on the part of the user.

    (1) By "use" we mean interaction with an object via its API. Interactions via other means (e.g. via Java Reflection) is out of the scope of this specification. Using a reference to an object (e.g. passing it between threads) is not considered to be a use of the object and generally requires additional synchronization.
